snippet: Investors were encouraged, but Wall Street, awaiting February’s employment report, maintained caution in the face of tensions over Ukraine.
abstract: Stocks move mostly higher, with Standard & Poor’s 500-stock index reaching yet another nominal record high, as investors seize on drop in initial jobless claims; overall sentiment remains cautious due to impending employment report and continued tensions in Ukraine.
lead_paragraph: Investors were encouraged, but Wall Street, awaiting February’s employment report, maintained caution in the face of tensions over Ukraine.

headline.main: Another S.&P. High as Market Mostly Rises
headline.print_headline: Another S.&P. High as Market Mostly Rises
